ngth`, `title-record-type-name`, `negative-zone-sign-nibble`, and `negative-pack-sign-nibble`. While the knowledge file does capture that UTF-8 is the default, the source's explicit recommendation to use UTF-8 unless there's a specific reason not to is a minor omission worth noting.\n\nThe critical gap is the default multiplicity rule—when no brackets are specified, an item defaults to `[1]`, meaning it appears exactly once. This is a fundamental constraint that could lead to incorrect implementations if misunderstood. The missing V4 hints are less severe.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22617,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22617,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06a95b38-3c2d-487e-a2c8-2275ec36adec","uuid":"8956ad03-36fa-4d40-98d0-9e1e79de2859"}
